|WKBClans: An Overview
|WKO------------------

|YKOClans are first and foremost a social medium, allowing players the ability
to form organized groups outside the confines of guilds. In addition to
the purely social aspect of clans, clans also add to the game by allowing for
clan warfare.

Non-warfare features of clans:
  |BKB-- |GKBClan channel
  |BKB-- |GKBClan headquarters
     |BKB** |GKBPlace to store items and equipment
     |BKB** |GKBPlace to deposit money into a shared clan coffers
  |BKB-- |GKBCustomized clan emote
  |BKB-- |GKBClan rankings and reputations|YKO

Warfare-specific features of clans:
  |BKB-- |GKBAbility to mutually agree to a war with another clan leader
  |BKB-- |GKBDetailed post-war information (# kills, best kill, etc)
  |BKB-- |GKBOpportunity to increase clan reputation rapidly
  |BKB-- |GKBAll clan wars are set in duration (minimum of 3 days)
  |BKB-- |GKBClan warfare ignores normal PK status (ie. Non-PKers can kill/be killed|YKO)

Please see |YKB"help clans basics" |YKOfor a more detailed intro to clans.
Please see |YKB"help clans war" |YKOfor warfare information.
Please see |YKB"help clans cmds" |YKOfor clan command information.
